cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with network data and proposes a novel approach for obtaining node embeddings in multi-layered networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses DeepWalk and fine-tuning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, respectively, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also evaluates its approach on node classification, link prediction, and community detection tasks, which are related to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with inferencing in multi-layered networks, which can be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
